Differentiation_protocol:
To allow
differentiation to a neuronal like phenotype, prior to treatments,
the cell cultures were split in 48-well plates at a density of 30×
103 cells/well, using the same environmental conditions in DMEM
medium with only 0.5% (v/v) fetal bovine serum (FBS), plus
antibiotics, supplemented with retinoic acid 10 μM, and maintained
until differentiated phenotype is clearly morphologically
observed (3–5) days.
